1
00:00:01,020 --> 00:00:03,020
Who the hell are you?

2
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:20,750
(Tarot readings
Come see your destiny)

3
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,260
You think this is my first time seeing a guy like you?

4
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:36,070
A guy like me?

5
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:37,300
What did I do?

6
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:38,290
Just because you’re a celebrity

7
00:00:38,290 --> 00:00:40,710
you think you can do whatever?

8
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:41,990
It’s you

9
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,450
The one sending creepy letters to my place

10
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:46,940
Following me around like a shadow
selling photos like some creep

11
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:48,260
That’s not me!

12
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:50,780
Alright alright everyone calm down

13
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:54,900
I’ve gotta get home and catch my cat show live

14
00:01:00,990 --> 00:01:03,490
Are you laughing at me right now?

15
00:01:03,490 --> 00:01:06,750
Well you are easy on the eyes at least

16
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:08,510
Good looking my ass…

17
00:01:08,510 --> 00:01:11,520
You look like a damn cat’s balls

18
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:13,160
Whoa! That’s verbal abuse!

19
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:14,020
That’s an insult!

20
00:01:14,020 --> 00:01:15,540
I’m suing him!

21
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:17,600
Geonwoo!!!

22
00:01:20,590 --> 00:01:21,810
A… are you okay?

23
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:23,370
W… wh… what happened?!

24
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:24,800
Call a lawyer

25
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:27,360
Uh yeah… I was gonna anyway…

26
00:01:27,740 --> 00:01:30,690
You think I don’t have a lawyer or what?

27
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:32,830
Why would you ever need a lawyer?

28
00:01:32,830 --> 00:01:34,300
This is exactly when you need one

29
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:36,440
I’ve got one too so just wait

30
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:43,070
(Law school kid! You’re finally useful
I’m being wronged. Send me your number)

31
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:46,330
Pick three cards

32
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,840
What?

33
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:49,910
But where are you..

34
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:51,790
Think of your question quietly

35
00:01:51,790 --> 00:01:54,490
Then draw three cards from the table

36
00:01:54,490 --> 00:01:56,490
Oh…

37
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:05,070
Will Jaeyeon ever like me?

38
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:26,010
Pick one more

39
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,880
Hmm… you’ll get exactly one chance

40
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,880
What?

41
00:02:36,810 --> 00:02:39,900
Miss that moment and you’ll be stuck as friends forever…

42
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,820
(Law school kid! You’re finally useful
I’m being wronged. Send me your number)

43
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:48,540
(Calling Jaeyeon)

44
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:55,740
It's twenty thousand won...

45
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:01,320
Lawyer! Over here!

46
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:02,560
Hey what happened?

47
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:05,890
Taewoo he keeps calling me a creep…

48
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:07,550
A stalker…!

49
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:09,920
Bro?

50
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:12,150
What is this?

51
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,950
You brought him here?

52
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:16,160
Bro?

53
00:03:16,490 --> 00:03:18,210
You

54
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:19,930
Did you get get to my brother?

55
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:20,970
Bullshit…

56
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:22,340
What the hell is going on

57
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,650
Yeah seriously…?

58
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:25,670
What is going on?

59
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:31,270
I’ve secured the CCTV footage

60
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:34,240
Can we take a look together?

61
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,300
Sure go ahead

62
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,270
This guy…

63
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:48,060
I don’t think he’s a creep…

64
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:55,600
Really?

65
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,120
Really…?

66
00:03:58,610 --> 00:03:59,830
This is your chance

67
00:03:59,830 --> 00:04:01,470
What…?

68
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,730
An interview

69
00:04:02,730 --> 00:04:04,500
Do an interview instead of an apology

70
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:08,470
I know my brother well

71
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,760
You won’t get a sincere apology anyway

72
00:04:10,770 --> 00:04:11,930
I can apologize on Geonwoo’s behalf..

73
00:04:11,940 --> 00:04:13,650
No it’s fine

74
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:17,180
Should we at least offer compensation?

75
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,820
Is a million won enough?

76
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:21,250
That’s better than an apology right?

77
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:27,190
No forget it…!

78
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:29,720
Just help me with one thing

79
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,290
Do it with me!

80
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,050
Do what…?

81
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:44,650
W… wh… what exactly?

82
00:04:44,650 --> 00:04:46,420
The interview… the interview!

83
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:49,120
He tends to trip over his words when he’s nervous…

84
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,430
Thirty minutes is enough!

85
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:52,790
Just thirty minutes for the interview

86
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:01,260
Tomorrow at four pm, at my place

87
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:03,370
Send him the address

88
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,750
About what just happened

89
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,770
I wanted to apologize on his behalf…

90
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,370
You didn’t do anything wrong sir

91
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,700
He can be like that sometimes

92
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:22,140
But he’s got his reasons

93
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:24,580
He is lucky

94
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:25,440
Huh?

95
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,740
He always have people on his side

96
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,460
Hey hey!

97
00:05:30,460 --> 00:05:31,770
I’m on your side!

98
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:33,100
I’ll always be on your side!

99
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:36,570
Yeah you better stay on my side forever

100
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,960
Here’s my number

101
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,110
Text me and I’ll send you the address

102
00:05:40,110 --> 00:05:42,020
Oh yes yes

103
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:44,040
Then…

104
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,270
Taewoo!

105
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,440
Yeah?

106
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:56,000
It’s not always like that

107
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,260
Huh?

108
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,650
Your brother...

109
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:04,630
Never mind… let’s meet again sometime

110
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:20,710
Are you an angel?

111
00:06:20,710 --> 00:06:21,600
I am indeed

112
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,170
Could you grant me the other side too?

113
00:06:24,170 --> 00:06:25,360
That’s a bit greedy

114
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,680
I thought you were an angel

115
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:29,200
You’re the kind who’d steal an angel’s underwear

116
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:36,770
Your text scared the hell out of me

117
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:38,460
When they said they were calling a lawyer

118
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:40,450
I got nervous too

119
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:41,680
So that’s why you said I was a lawyer?

120
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:43,480
Yeah

121
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:45,040
That’s fraud you know

122
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,050
I don’t care

123
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:49,180
It worked out so whatever

124
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:54,810
So why is it awkward between you and your brother?

125
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:57,340
You saw the reason yourself

126
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:59,630
Yeah I guess so..

127
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:03,700
You know my parents got divorced right?

128
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,520
Yeah I know

129
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,290
Did you know my dad went to prison and got out?

130
00:07:07,290 --> 00:07:09,540
I didn’t… huh?

131
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,560
Sorry sorry sorry

132
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,250
Did I catch you off guard?

133
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,210
I mean it is kind of shocking

134
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:16,380
But why?

135
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,820
My brother reported our dad

136
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:19,510
What?

137
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:25,710
After my parents divorced

138
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,420
my brother took off as a child actor

139
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:30,650
my mom was always following him around

140
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:36,580
My dad would still come by sometimes to hang out with me…

141
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,170
At least I had my dad

142
00:07:38,170 --> 00:07:40,610
I think I felt less lonely…

143
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:44,490
But maybe my dad missed my brother too

144
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,570
He kept taking him without saying anything

145
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:51,680
Hey… is it okay for me to hear this?

146
00:07:51,690 --> 00:07:54,840
If not you then who would listen

147
00:07:56,840 --> 00:08:00,810
My mom and my brother reported my dad

148
00:08:00,810 --> 00:08:03,240
And he ended up going to prison

149
00:08:04,090 --> 00:08:06,190
My grandma was the one who told me

150
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:09,260
So I don’t really know the full truth…

151
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:12,890
Were you… okay?

152
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,050
No

153
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,230
My mom started protecting my brother even more

154
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:29,240
And I was left alone for longer

155
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:34,280
Honestly my brother didn’t do anything wrong

156
00:08:35,170 --> 00:08:37,430
But it felt like he took my mom and dad away

157
00:08:37,430 --> 00:08:39,060
So I just ended up resenting him

158
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:41,840
I sound really immature right?

159
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,290
No!

160
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:45,320
Not at all!

161
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:50,520
You turned out just fine

162
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:53,550
And honestly you’re way better looking than your brother

163
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:55,680
You’re smart too

164
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:58,580
Right

165
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,630
I’m the best huh?

166
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,530
Huh?!

167
00:09:00,530 --> 00:09:01,800
Yeah alright

168
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:23,070
Um… hey!

169
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:29,030
Um… can I get an autograph…

170
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:35,370
I’m Noh Jaeil

171
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,680
Thank you!

172
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:50,160
(William)

173
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,680
That bastard..

174
00:09:57,330 --> 00:10:01,060
You’re curious about the cards he picked?

175
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:11,800
The first card means affection without romance
More like friendship or family warmth

176
00:10:11,810 --> 00:10:16,900
The second card is agape love
Too deep to be just friends but not quite lovers

177
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:24,510
The last card means they become like family
but won’t end up as lovers

178
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:27,300
What about the extra card he drew?

179
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:36,350
That was a chance I gave him, It means he’ll get one shot
Whether he can take it… I don’t know

180
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,910
Why are you being so friendly..?

181
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:39,570
Thirty thousand won

182
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:40,680
You said twenty earlier

183
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,200
Thirty thousand…
